data.text:
Eye on China & Pakistan, India fast-tracks deal for 31 US 'hunter-killer' drones

tnn / Aug 14, 2024, 07:29 (IST)

India accelerated talks to acquire 31 weaponised MQ-9B drones from the US, aiming for a deal by year-end. This move comes amid China and Pakistan enhancing their armed drone capabilities. The drones will support India's military, with assembly and some components sourced locally. The deal's cost negotiations are ongoing, with efforts to finalize it soon.

IED movement from Jammu? Ahead of Independence Day, fidayeen attack alert in Delhi

tnn / Aug 14, 2024, 07:40 (IST)

The intelligence community has remained on high alert due to information about operatives from a terrorist group in Jammu potentially planning a fidayeen attack in Delhi or Punjab around Independence Day. Security measures have been intensified, particularly for the celebrations and the President's 'At Home' reception, amidst reports of explosives and potential high-profile targets.

Watch: How Sachin celebrated 'International Left-Handers Day'

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 06:28 (IST)

Sachin Tendulkar showcased his left-handed batting skills in celebration of International Left-Handers Day. Despite being primarily right-handed, Tendulkar has shown versatility by occasionally practicing left-arm spin. His video on social media highlighted his ability to play delightful shots with his left hand, impressing fans and celebrating left-handed individuals worldwide.

'Cautionary tale for ... ': What Vivek Ramaswamy said on violence against Hindus in Bangladesh

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 08:01 (IST)

Vivek Ramaswamy, a former Republican presidential candidate, condemned the violence against Hindus in Bangladesh following Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's ouster. He criticized the quota system implemented after the 1971 independence war, which he argued led to protests and the government's collapse. Ramaswamy highlighted that radicals are now targeting Hindu minorities amidst the political turmoil.

All are equal, will protect your rights, Muhammad Yunus assures Hindus

tnn / Aug 14, 2024, 01:31 (IST)

Bangladesh's interim chief adviser Prof Muhammad Yunus assured equal rights for the Hindu community amid recent unrest. During a visit to Dhakeshwari temple, he emphasized the need for unity and fixing institutional decay. Thousands of Hindus protested for safety following attacks since Sheikh Hasina's government fell on August 5. A hotline for reporting attacks was established.

Have we stopped caring about what happens in public hospitals?

Aug 13, 2024, 21:21 (IST)

The aftermath of the Kolkata doctor's rape-murder has unmasked several issues – state of public hospitals, resident doctors’ poor working conditions and the precarious position of women even in a field they now dominate by number

Remove these Amul videos: Delhi High Court to YT, FB and Instagram

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 00:49 (IST)

The Delhi High Court ordered a Noida resident to remove defamatory videos about Amul products from social media. This followed a viral claim of a centipede found in an Amul ice cream tub. Non-compliance led to the court directing platforms like X, YouTube, and Meta to take down the content within 36 hours.

Biden says he would attend Trump inauguration if he wins: 'I have good manners'

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 01:08 (IST)

President Joe Biden Tuesday said he would attend Donald Trump's inauguration in January in case the Republican presidential candidate wins this year's election. "I have good manners, not like him," Biden told reporters after being asked if he'd attend. Trump did not attend Biden's inauguration in 2021. It was the first time in over 150 years that the outgoing president skipped the new president's swearing in.
